sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client Application
    participant KServe as KServe / Istio Gateway
    participant gRPC as Caikit gRPC Server<br/>8085/TCP TLS/mTLS
    participant HTTP as Caikit HTTP Server<br/>8080/TCP TLS/mTLS
    participant Predict as GlobalPredictServicer
    participant Train as GlobalTrainServicer
    participant MM as ModelMesh Controller
    participant MRS as ModelRuntimeServicer
    participant MgrCore as Model Manager (core)
    participant Module as Module.run() / .load() / .train()
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Metrics as Metrics Server<br/>8086/TCP HTTP
    participant OTEL as OTLP Collector<br/>4317/4318/TCP
    participant Probe as caikit-health-probe
    participant Kubelet as Kubernetes kubelet

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over Client,Module: Flow 1: Model Inference (gRPC)
        Client->>gRPC: gRPC inference request<br/>TLS/mTLS (configurable)
        gRPC->>Predict: CaikitRuntimeServerWrapper<br/>routes RPC
        Predict->>MgrCore: retrieve_model(model_id)
        MgrCore->>Module: Module.run(input)
        Module-->>MgrCore: prediction result
        MgrCore-->>Predict: result
        Predict->>Metrics: record RPC metrics<br/>HTTP/8086 plaintext
        Predict->>OTEL: export trace span<br/>OTLP gRPC/4317
        Predict-->>gRPC: response
        gRPC-->>Client: gRPC response
    end

    rect rgb(230, 255, 230)
        Note over Client,Module: Flow 2: Model Inference (HTTP)
        Client->>HTTP: POST /api/v1/task/{task_name}<br/>HTTPS/mTLS (configurable)
        HTTP->>Predict: predict_model()
        Predict->>MgrCore: retrieve_model(model_id)
        MgrCore->>Module: Module.run(input)
        Module-->>MgrCore: prediction result
        MgrCore-->>Predict: result
        Predict-->>HTTP: JSON response
        HTTP-->>Client: HTTP 200 + JSON body
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over MM,S3: Flow 3: Model Loading (ModelMesh)
        MM->>MRS: loadModel(model_id, model_path)<br/>unix:///tmp/mmesh/grpc.sock<br/>plaintext (pod-local)
        MRS->>MgrCore: load_model(model_id, path)
        MgrCore->>MgrCore: LocalModelFinder<br/>resolve local path
        MgrCore->>Module: Module.load(model_path, backend)
        Module-->>MgrCore: loaded model instance
        MgrCore-->>MRS: model loaded + size
        MRS-->>MM: ModelInfo(sizeInBytes)
    end

    rect rgb(255, 230, 230)
        Note over Client,S3: Flow 4: Training Job
        Client->>gRPC: training request<br/>gRPC/8085 or HTTP/8080
        gRPC->>Train: GlobalTrainServicer
        Train->>Train: LocalModelTrainer<br/>spawn thread/subprocess
        Train->>Module: Module.train(data_stream)
        Module->>S3: fetch training data<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>AWS IAM credentials
        S3-->>Module: data artifacts
        Module->>Module: training execution
        Module->>S3: save trained model<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
        Module-->>Train: training complete
        Train-->>gRPC: training_id + status
        gRPC-->>Client: training response
    end

    rect rgb(245, 230, 255)
        Note over Kubelet,HTTP: Flow 5: Health Probe
        Kubelet->>Probe: exec liveness/readiness check
        Probe->>HTTP: GET /health<br/>HTTP/HTTPS 8080/TCP<br/>TLS matches server config
        HTTP-->>Probe: 200 OK
        Probe->>gRPC: grpc.health.v1.Health.Check<br/>8085/TCP or unix socket<br/>TLS matches server config
        gRPC-->>Probe: SERVING
        Probe-->>Kubelet: exit 0 (healthy)
    end
